{#- LLM-facing text is English-only: Cyrillic uses roughly 2–3× more tokens per word.
    This Jinja comment is stripped and never sent to the model.
    docs/ARCHITECTURE.md §6.2: tool-spec for route `cli_intent`. -#}
{
  "type": "function",
  "function": {
    "name": "cli_intent",
    "description": "Request shell execution via CLI pipeline (allow/deny/HITL). Use for external effects, live system state, or read-only discovery on the agent host. Discovery (read-only): before creating or editing files, inventory existing code with rg, find, cat, head, ls; git read-only only (git grep, git log, git show) — never git commit/push/reset without explicit user request. One argv array per call (no shell chaining). Safety: non-interactive flags; limit output; no destructive commands without explicit user request; no secrets in argv.\n\nWhen NOT to use: a fact retrievable from the knowledge graph → memory_query first; broad multi-step repo survey → subagent_intent with an inventory-only task. Cost/latency: commands may route through allow/deny policy or HITL — keep each command single-purpose.\n\nDiscovery examples: [\"rg\", \"-l\", \"EmailBridge\", \"ansible/roles/threlium/files/scripts/threlium/bridges\"], [\"find\", \"ansible/roles/threlium/files/scripts/threlium\", \"-name\", \"*bridge*\"], [\"cat\", \"path/to/existing.py\"]. Implementation example: [\"pip\", \"install\", \"--no-input\", \"ruff\"].",
    "parameters": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "argv": {
          "type": "array",
          "items": {"type": "string", "minLength": 1, "maxLength": 4000},
          "minItems": 1,
          "maxItems": 64,
          "description": "Command and arguments as argv array (no shell escape; argv[0] is binary name)."
        },
        "cwd": {
          "type": "string",
          "maxLength": 4000,
          "description": "Working directory for execution (optional)."
        },
        "reasoning": {
          "type": "string",
          "minLength": 1,
          "maxLength": 2000,
          "description": "Why this command is needed — short text for logs and HITL confirmation."
        }
      },
      "required": ["argv", "reasoning"],
      "additionalProperties": false
    }
  }
}
